((SELECT id FROM crops WHERE label = 'Mustard' and zone = 6),(SELECT id FROM data_keys WHERE label = 'zone_cover_crop_description'),'Similar to other brassicas. Often used for pest suppression and adding diversity to mixes. Most bio-toxic compounds, best brassica for bio-fumigation (tissue must be chopped and tilled into soil). With fertility, potential for fast fall growth, high biomass, good N scavenging. Not known for subsoiling, some varieties may not have taproot. Winter-hardiness, day-length response (i.e. flowering trigger), other characteristics may vary by cultivar. Research and match varieties to your need. Descr. modified from C. Lawrence, VA NRCS Cover Crop Planning Manual.
'),
