((SELECT id FROM crops WHERE label = 'Phacelia' and zone = 6),(SELECT id FROM data_keys WHERE label = 'cover_crop_description'),'Unique forb with fernlike biomass. Not commonly grown in the Northeast US (well-known in Europe), info limited, seed costly. Winter-kill generally expected. Fast growth in mild temperatures, moderate biomass, residue not long-lasting. Fibrous shallow roots excellent for soil aggregation. Appears to have daylength response: in fall vegetative growth only; in spring goes to flower. Given that it rarely survives the winter, may do best if planted in spring when blooms are of interest. Showy blue blooms are excellent for pollinators.  
