((SELECT id FROM crops WHERE label = 'Rapeseed, Forage' and zone = 6),(SELECT id FROM data_keys WHERE label = 'cover_crop_description'),'Excellent fall-planted cover crop choice. Generally winter-hardy if seeded during the optimum planting window; cultivars vary in cold hardiness. With adequate residual soil fertility, provides good biomass, forage, deep branched taproot, N scavenging, weed suppression. Host for sclerotinia, so caution when planting prior to legumes. Spring flowers attract pollinators. Low cost to seed. Range of cultivar choices (canola for seed, hybrids for grazing, etc.), characteristics may differ by cultivar. Contributes pollinator food source to mixes, but plant at low end of seeding rate to prevent it from outcompeting other cover crops in the mix. Hard to kill in late spring with herbicides. “Dwarf Essex” is a commonly-grown cultivar.
